      • getMeanLine

        public SVGElement getMeanLine(SVGLine line,
                              Angle angleEps)
        creates a mean line.

        averages the point at end of the two lines. If lines are parallel use XY(0) and line.XY(0), as first/from point. If antiparallel use XY(0) and line.XY(1). Similarly second/to uses XY(1) and line.XY(1) for parallel and XY(1) and line.XY(0) for antiparallel. Mean line is always aligned with line 0.

        Does not check for overlap of lines - that's up to the user to decide the cases. Does not add any style

        Parameters:
        line -
        angleEps - to test whether anti/parallel
        Returns:
        null if lines not parallel
